WEBVTT

1
00:00:45.611 --> 00:00:47.239 line:82%
The armies of India and Pakistan...

2
00:00:47.427 --> 00:00:49.974 line:82%
...have fought four wars in
the past sixty years...

3
00:00:51.986 --> 00:00:55.682 line:82%
...but there are two government
agencies in these two countries...

4
00:00:55.954 --> 00:00:58.236 line:82%
...that are at war every day,
every moment.

5
00:00:58.569 --> 00:01:01.486 line:82%
India's RAW and Pakistan's ISI.

6
00:01:04.444 --> 00:01:07.111 line:82%
The common man does not get
any news about these agencies...

7
00:01:07.444 --> 00:01:09.361 line:82%
...because in the name
of national security...

8
00:01:09.652 --> 00:01:11.688 line:82%
...all information is forever guarded.

9
00:01:12.986 --> 00:01:17.185 line:82%
But there are some stories that
escape these walls and office files.

10
00:01:18.444 --> 00:01:22.111 line:82%
This is the story that shook the very
foundations of this secretive world.

11
00:01:24.569 --> 00:01:27.264 line:82%
This is the story of Tiger.

12
00:01:28.835 --> 00:01:31.853 line:82%
ZAKHO - NORTHERN IRAQ
0530 HRS

13
00:03:40.236 --> 00:03:41.522 line:82%
Goodbye.

14
00:03:55.694 --> 00:03:56.736 line:82%
Tiger?

15
00:04:10.277 --> 00:04:11.819 line:82%
Hello... hello...
Those people are here.

16
00:04:12.069 --> 00:04:13.936 line:82%
I told you they would find me!

17
00:04:14.486 --> 00:04:16.073 line:82%
They found me!

18
00:04:16.243 --> 00:04:19.361 line:82%
You've kept me here for over a month.
Now get me out of here!

19
00:04:19.986 --> 00:04:21.986 line:82%
Tell me quickly...
what should I do? Tell me.

20
00:04:22.236 --> 00:04:24.504 line:82%
Okay. I'll get there...
you get there too!

21
00:05:23.486 --> 00:05:26.069 line:82%
You're panting like a dog...
how much do you smoke?

22
00:05:26.902 --> 00:05:30.534 line:82%
I can't believe you sold
out to them, Rabinder...

23
00:05:33.393 --> 00:05:34.729 line:82%
How much did the ISI pay?

24
00:05:34.902 --> 00:05:37.426 line:82%
Tiger... how much does
the government job pay us?

25
00:05:40.527 --> 00:05:42.216 line:82%
What is the going price
for buying agents these days?

26
00:05:43.111 --> 00:05:45.620 line:82%
It's a lot, Tiger! Trust me...
there is a lot of money!

27
00:05:46.152 --> 00:05:51.371 line:82%
Should be... after all you
sold information to the ISI...

28
00:05:52.069 --> 00:05:54.569 line:82%
...the guys who kill our
agents almost every day.

29
00:05:54.902 --> 00:05:56.751 line:82%
So? Even we smash those guys.

30
00:05:56.942 --> 00:05:59.434 line:82%
How many ISI men have you
killed in your career alone?

31
00:06:00.861 --> 00:06:05.069 line:82%
This is a game, Tiger...
we are the smallest pawns in it.

32
00:06:05.361 --> 00:06:06.848 line:82%
Please understand.

33
00:06:09.444 --> 00:06:11.069 line:82%
I'll show you...

34
00:06:16.319 --> 00:06:18.444 line:82%
Look at this, Tiger!

35
00:06:19.277 --> 00:06:21.430 line:82%
Just see. Will RAW ever give us this?

36
00:06:24.402 --> 00:06:27.902 line:82%
Just see this, Tiger.

37
00:06:28.361 --> 00:06:31.071 line:82%
This is... almost two months' salary.

38
00:06:31.319 --> 00:06:32.697 line:82%
What good is it, Tiger?

39
00:06:32.944 --> 00:06:36.277 line:82%
One fine day we'll end up dead...
in some obscure part of the world...

40
00:06:36.486 --> 00:06:39.409 line:82%
...and no one will come
to claim our bodies.

41
00:06:39.694 --> 00:06:41.576 line:82%
Come with me, Tiger...
there's a lot of money to be made...

42
00:06:41.777 --> 00:06:43.486 line:82%
...there's nothing
in all these issues.

43
00:06:47.944 --> 00:06:48.973 line:82%
Sorry, Rabinder...

44
00:06:51.763 --> 00:06:52.819 line:82%
...you will have to come with me.

45
00:06:52.988 --> 00:06:53.944 line:82%
I'm not going, Tiger!

46
00:06:54.111 --> 00:06:55.944 line:82%
I won't go with you...
I'm telling you, I won't.

47
00:06:57.236 --> 00:06:57.902 line:82%
Alive...

48
00:07:00.236 --> 00:07:00.986 line:82%
...or dead.

49
00:12:58.027 --> 00:12:59.361 line:82%
He's back!

50
00:12:59.611 --> 00:13:00.402 line:82%
The hero returns...

51
00:13:00.652 --> 00:13:02.443 line:82%
He has shown up after many days.

52
00:13:02.694 --> 00:13:04.814 line:82%
Hey, look... He's back again...

53
00:13:07.569 --> 00:13:09.506 line:82%
Why are you so happy?

54
00:13:09.861 --> 00:13:12.960 line:82%
I'm not happy. I'm just telling you.

55
00:13:13.319 --> 00:13:14.361 line:82%
Look at his face...

56
00:13:14.569 --> 00:13:15.736 line:82%
He must have been in a brawl.

57
00:13:16.027 --> 00:13:17.363 line:82%
He goes missing for months...

58
00:13:17.553 --> 00:13:20.072 line:82%
...how can you even think of getting
him married to our dear Bablee?

59
00:13:23.277 --> 00:13:24.819 line:82%
Why are you staring at him?

60
00:13:25.017 --> 00:13:26.279 line:82%
I'm not staring at him.

61
00:13:26.459 --> 00:13:27.665 line:82%
Do your exercise!

62
00:13:27.861 --> 00:13:28.986 line:82%
But what does he do?

63
00:13:29.194 --> 00:13:30.552 line:82%
How the hell should I know?

64
00:13:30.752 --> 00:13:32.611 line:82%
But he's a Grade 1 officer.

65
00:13:54.091 --> 00:13:57.150 line:82%
Hello, sonny... it's nine already...
let me give you a lift to the office.

66
00:13:57.338 --> 00:13:58.560 line:82%
Thank you, Mr Bagga.

67
00:13:58.740 --> 00:13:59.444 line:82%
Come...

68
00:13:59.652 --> 00:14:01.824 line:82%
I had a briefing with
Mr Shenoy at nine.

69
00:14:02.194 --> 00:14:04.801 line:82%
Oh, Mr Shenoy is extremely punctual.

70
00:14:07.861 --> 00:14:10.907 line:82%
Sir, Rabinder was kept
near Iraq's Northern border...

71
00:14:11.194 --> 00:14:14.206 line:82%
I had information that the ISI
might move him any time.

72
00:14:14.486 --> 00:14:15.817 line:82%
We caught him at the right time.

73
00:14:16.111 --> 00:14:17.078 line:82%
Good Job, Tiger.

74
00:14:17.611 --> 00:14:18.194 line:82%
Thank you, sir.

75
00:14:18.402 --> 00:14:19.402 line:82%
As usual.

76
00:14:20.861 --> 00:14:22.236 line:82%
Submit the full report to Tiwari.

77
00:14:22.861 --> 00:14:23.569 line:82%
Yes, Sir.

78
00:14:26.027 --> 00:14:26.652 line:82%
Tiger.

79
00:14:26.815 --> 00:14:27.480 line:82%
Yes, sir?

80
00:14:27.809 --> 00:14:29.736 line:82%
Your face is badly bruised.

81
00:14:30.361 --> 00:14:31.861 line:82%
Why don't you go on
leave and rest for a bit?

82
00:14:32.111 --> 00:14:33.569 line:82%
Sir, I'll be fine in a couple of days.

83
00:14:33.819 --> 00:14:34.861 line:82%
Why do I need to go on leave?

84
00:14:35.111 --> 00:14:37.986 line:82%
You've been on assignments
back to back for 12 years now.

85
00:14:38.181 --> 00:14:39.831 line:82%
That's way too long.

86
00:14:40.236 --> 00:14:41.861 line:82%
Don't tempt fate.

87
00:14:42.236 --> 00:14:44.069 line:82%
Sir, one fine day I'll find
myself posted to a desk job...

88
00:14:44.402 --> 00:14:46.950 line:82%
...reading files... just like you do.

89
00:14:47.611 --> 00:14:48.821 line:82%
Alright...

90
00:14:49.111 --> 00:14:51.427 line:82%
...as soon as you look normal again...

91
00:14:51.694 --> 00:14:53.069 line:82%
...you can leave for
your next assignment.

92
00:14:54.194 --> 00:14:55.152 line:82%
Where, sir?

93
00:14:55.444 --> 00:14:57.944 line:82%
Why don't you treat me
to your famous daal...

94
00:14:58.736 --> 00:15:02.098 line:82%
...then I'll find you an enemy
in a new country.

95
00:15:02.569 --> 00:15:03.319 line:82%
Done, sir.

96
00:15:06.902 --> 00:15:08.986 line:82%
Sir, I often get this feeling that...

97
00:15:09.277 --> 00:15:13.149 line:82%
...you hired me at RAW purely
for my cooking skills.

98
00:15:13.611 --> 00:15:15.963 line:82%
You're right.
For your cooking skills...

99
00:15:16.111 --> 00:15:17.819 line:82%
...and your insanity.

100
00:15:19.194 --> 00:15:21.433 line:82%
How do you live like this, Tiger?

101
00:15:21.694 --> 00:15:23.671 line:82%
This decade old furniture...

102
00:15:23.902 --> 00:15:26.803 line:82%
...no pictures or books or anything?

103
00:15:27.277 --> 00:15:29.369 line:82%
Your salary has been
lying untouched...

104
00:15:29.561 --> 00:15:32.640 line:82%
...in the agency's salary
account for the last 8 years.

105
00:15:33.694 --> 00:15:34.819 line:82%
Why?

106
00:15:35.444 --> 00:15:37.324 line:82%
How can I spend when I'm never here?

107
00:15:37.569 --> 00:15:38.986 line:82%
I have been traveling
all over the world...

108
00:15:39.236 --> 00:15:40.983 line:82%
...for the past 12 years
on government funds.

109
00:15:41.152 --> 00:15:43.777 line:82%
Wow. How much have you saved?

110
00:15:44.486 --> 00:15:46.944 line:82%
About 2.3 million.

111
00:15:50.944 --> 00:15:53.236 line:82%
But your money will rot
in the agency's bank...

112
00:15:54.652 --> 00:15:58.992 line:82%
No, Sir. The day I retire from
this job. I'll blow it all up.

113
00:16:01.736 --> 00:16:04.962 line:82%
Why didn't you ever have a girlfriend?

114
00:16:05.611 --> 00:16:07.255 line:82%
Sir, how could I have one?

115
00:16:07.569 --> 00:16:10.979 line:82%
Firstly I'm never here and
secondly this goddamn job.

116
00:16:11.236 --> 00:16:13.986 line:82%
What's wrong with the job?

117
00:16:14.486 --> 00:16:18.090 line:82%
Sir, we have no answers
when someone asks.

118
00:16:18.361 --> 00:16:19.319 line:82%
What do you do?

119
00:16:19.527 --> 00:16:20.527 line:82%
I'm in the civil service.

120
00:16:20.736 --> 00:16:21.527 line:82%
What exactly is your job?

121
00:16:21.694 --> 00:16:22.486 line:82%
I'm in administration.

122
00:16:22.652 --> 00:16:23.569 line:82%
What is your duty?

123
00:16:23.777 --> 00:16:24.486 line:82%
Government duty.

124
00:16:24.694 --> 00:16:25.444 line:82%
But what do you do?

125
00:16:25.777 --> 00:16:26.611 line:82%
Nothing as of now.

126
00:16:27.277 --> 00:16:30.319 line:82%
Sir, sometimes I feel like
screaming and saying.

127
00:16:30.569 --> 00:16:31.944 line:82%
I'm a spy. A RAW Agent!!

128
00:16:32.194 --> 00:16:33.319 line:82%
Spy. Secret Agent!!

129
00:16:33.569 --> 00:16:35.081 line:82%
I'm James Bond!!

130
00:16:37.736 --> 00:16:39.861 line:82%
Sir, I still have time.
What about you?

131
00:16:40.611 --> 00:16:42.104 line:82%
Why didn't you ever get married?

132
00:16:42.444 --> 00:16:47.111 line:82%
When I was young...
I was a bit of a poet.

133
00:16:47.861 --> 00:16:53.152 line:82%
...and poets don't settle for arranged
marriages. They look for love.

134
00:16:54.486 --> 00:16:55.861 line:82%
Did you find love, Sir?

135
00:16:57.152 --> 00:16:59.236 line:82%
Yes. I did... once.

136
00:17:00.152 --> 00:17:01.277 line:82%
Wow!

137
00:17:03.444 --> 00:17:04.611 line:82%
Who was she, Sir?

138
00:17:07.319 --> 00:17:11.236 line:82%
Well, she was this sweet simple girl.

139
00:17:13.402 --> 00:17:20.033 line:82%
When I met her...
I wanted to live my life only for her.

140
00:17:22.402 --> 00:17:23.611 line:82%
And then?

141
00:17:24.694 --> 00:17:29.319 line:82%
Then... my goddamn duty
got in the way.

142
00:17:30.277 --> 00:17:34.944 line:82%
And you chose your duty over love?

143
00:17:35.486 --> 00:17:39.527 line:82%
Of course. Isn't that
what we're trained for?

144
00:17:41.194 --> 00:17:45.032 line:82%
But do you ever regret it, sir?

145
00:17:46.694 --> 00:17:51.264 line:82%
Every day, Tiger. Every single day.

146
00:17:58.319 --> 00:18:01.115 line:82%
Hello... yes, Nambiar.

147
00:18:04.111 --> 00:18:06.457 line:82%
Right, right... thank you.

148
00:18:08.944 --> 00:18:11.192 line:82%
It seems we've found
you your next mission.

149
00:18:12.777 --> 00:18:13.861 line:82%
Cheers, sir!

150
00:18:16.236 --> 00:18:17.777 line:82%
Between India and Pakistan...

151
00:18:18.303 --> 00:18:22.276 line:82%
...only India has an
anti-missile system that...

152
00:18:22.652 --> 00:18:27.335 line:82%
...can stop incoming Pakistani
missiles to a large extent.

153
00:18:27.694 --> 00:18:31.527 line:82%
And one man has played
a big role in developing it...

154
00:18:32.611 --> 00:18:35.156 line:82%
Professor Anwar Jamaal Kidwai.

155
00:18:35.611 --> 00:18:38.236 line:82%
A scientist who is well known
all over the world...

156
00:18:38.736 --> 00:18:41.861 line:82%
...but he's a maverick... that's why
he quit his government job...

157
00:18:42.232 --> 00:18:45.440 line:82%
...and started teaching at the famous
Trinity College in Dublin, Ireland.

158
00:18:45.777 --> 00:18:49.575 line:82%
But for the last few months
we suspect that Professor Kidwai...

159
00:18:49.940 --> 00:18:54.240 line:82%
...has been sharing his research
findings with other scientists...

160
00:18:54.569 --> 00:18:57.944 line:82%
...who could be working for the
Pakistan defence establishment.

161
00:19:02.527 --> 00:19:04.027 line:82%
So I must stop him?

162
00:19:04.736 --> 00:19:09.607 line:82%
No, Tiger. Like I said,
we only suspect him.

163
00:19:09.902 --> 00:19:12.400 line:82%
All you need to do is observe him.

164
00:19:13.902 --> 00:19:15.129 line:82%
Tiger...

165
00:19:15.652 --> 00:19:17.694 line:82%
Please don't kill anyone here.

166
00:19:18.111 --> 00:19:18.986 line:82%
Right, sir.

167
00:19:19.611 --> 00:19:23.327 line:82%
Every mission of yours
someone gets killed.

168
00:19:24.402 --> 00:19:26.970 line:82%
Please just observe him. Okay?

169
00:19:27.694 --> 00:19:29.068 line:82%
Okay, sir.

170
00:19:34.269 --> 00:19:35.420 line:82%
Good morning, Professor.

171
00:19:44.986 --> 00:19:47.750 line:82%
Professor Kidwai...
what an honour to meet you.

172
00:19:48.069 --> 00:19:51.845 line:82%
I park there every day. It's my spot.

173
00:19:52.152 --> 00:19:53.387 line:82%
Sure, sir.

174
00:19:59.527 --> 00:20:00.444 line:82%
Professor Kidwai...

175
00:20:01.027 --> 00:20:03.488 line:82%
Professor! Professor Kidwai?

176
00:20:03.861 --> 00:20:05.277 line:82%
No time, no time.

177
00:20:08.777 --> 00:20:10.318 line:82%
Pleasure meeting you.

178
00:20:58.861 --> 00:21:00.687 line:82%
Good afternoon, Professor Kidwai!

179
00:21:00.944 --> 00:21:01.819 line:82%
Hello!

180
00:21:02.361 --> 00:21:04.736 line:82%
Professor, I have to speak with you
about something important.

181
00:21:05.111 --> 00:21:06.798 line:82%
Sorry, I've got to feed the dog.

182
00:21:07.088 --> 00:21:09.110 line:82%
After feeding doggy?

183
00:21:09.486 --> 00:21:11.232 line:82%
I won't take too much of your time...

184
00:21:11.819 --> 00:21:13.024 line:82%
Sorry!

185
00:21:14.527 --> 00:21:16.478 line:82%
This professor is a nutcase.

186
00:21:21.486 --> 00:21:23.569 line:82%
Professor... Professor...

187
00:21:23.902 --> 00:21:25.561 line:82%
Professor. I won't take up
too much time.

188
00:21:27.069 --> 00:21:28.902 line:82%
Sorry... got to take Rocket out.

189
00:21:29.402 --> 00:21:31.297 line:82%
Shall I wait here?

190
00:21:31.694 --> 00:21:32.861 line:82%
Rocket!

191
00:21:48.402 --> 00:21:49.444 line:82%
Rocket!

192
00:22:44.833 --> 00:22:45.469 line:82%
Hey!

193
00:22:48.777 --> 00:22:52.927 line:82%
There's one girl who has access
to the professor's house.

194
00:22:53.319 --> 00:22:57.456 line:82%
A British girl of Indian origin. Zoya.

195
00:22:57.944 --> 00:23:01.447 line:82%
A student of Trinity Dance Academy
for a year now.

196
00:23:01.777 --> 00:23:04.361 line:82%
And a part-time caretaker
of his house.

197
00:23:04.581 --> 00:23:06.027 line:82%
Get out! You really cannot be here.

198
00:23:06.236 --> 00:23:08.364 line:82%
Sorry. I'm sorry. Relax.
I really didn't mean to. Excuse.

199
00:23:08.549 --> 00:23:09.845 line:82%
Will you please leave!

200
00:23:23.194 --> 00:23:24.097 line:82%
You're still here?

201
00:23:24.267 --> 00:23:26.484 line:82%
Yes... waiting for the mad professor.

202
00:23:27.736 --> 00:23:30.468 line:82%
Next time ring the bell...
or I'll get you arrested.

203
00:23:31.152 --> 00:23:31.795 line:82%
Sorry, Miss.

204
00:23:32.513 --> 00:23:33.350 line:82%
Does he know you?

205
00:23:34.194 --> 00:23:36.076 line:82%
No. I have come from India.

206
00:23:37.769 --> 00:23:39.771 line:82%
It's difficult to say
when he'll be back.

207
00:23:41.894 --> 00:23:43.019 line:82%
This is his house, right?

208
00:23:44.444 --> 00:23:47.309 line:82%
Yes... but he goes for
long walks with Rocket.

209
00:23:49.277 --> 00:23:50.924 line:82%
Hope he hasn't gone to London.

210
00:23:51.194 --> 00:23:53.861 line:82%
I've just come from there.
I could have met him there.

211
00:23:58.140 --> 00:24:00.586 line:82%
I'm sorry... he's troubled me all day.

212
00:24:03.444 --> 00:24:04.299 line:82%
Very funny.

213
00:24:06.986 --> 00:24:10.573 line:82%
Excuse me. I don't know anyone here.

214
00:24:11.027 --> 00:24:12.407 line:82%
Is there a hotel around somewhere?

215
00:24:14.930 --> 00:24:17.378 line:82%
They're on my way. Come on.

216
00:24:18.611 --> 00:24:20.370 line:82%
We've not been introduced as yet.

217
00:24:20.777 --> 00:24:23.518 line:82%
I'm Zoya... Friends call me Zee.

218
00:24:24.569 --> 00:24:28.449 line:82%
I'm Manish Chandra...
My friends call me Doordarshan.

219
00:24:29.190 --> 00:24:30.027 line:82%
What?

220
00:24:30.236 --> 00:24:31.986 line:82%
Zee... Doordarshan?

221
00:24:33.944 --> 00:24:35.938 line:82%
That was a terrible joke.

222
00:24:38.736 --> 00:24:42.553 line:82%
Sorry... it was seriously rotten.

223
00:24:47.111 --> 00:24:48.440 line:82%
Check this one.

224
00:24:51.777 --> 00:24:53.111 line:82%
Excuse me... do you have any rooms?

225
00:24:53.486 --> 00:24:54.652 line:82%
Yes I believe we do, sir.

226
00:24:55.194 --> 00:24:56.694 line:82%
Thank you. Looking very lovely today.

227
00:24:56.861 --> 00:24:57.945 line:82%
Thank you.

228
00:25:02.486 --> 00:25:03.319 line:82%
No rooms.

229
00:25:07.319 --> 00:25:08.361 line:82%
Try here.

230
00:25:12.694 --> 00:25:13.777 line:82%
Good evening.

231
00:25:14.152 --> 00:25:15.277 line:82%
Good evening, sir.

232
00:25:16.569 --> 00:25:17.736 line:82%
Can I help you?

233
00:25:18.402 --> 00:25:19.944 line:82%
My name is Manish Chandra.

234
00:25:21.194 --> 00:25:23.163 line:82%
- Nice to meet you.
- Thank you.

235
00:25:27.569 --> 00:25:28.986 line:82%
This hotel is over-booked.

236
00:25:29.486 --> 00:25:31.319 line:82%
Okay. Listen my hostel is here...

237
00:25:31.569 --> 00:25:33.874 line:82%
...but there are a couple of hotels
ahead. Try them if you like.

238
00:25:34.361 --> 00:25:36.201 line:82%
Sure. Thank you.

239
00:26:31.236 --> 00:26:32.861 line:82%
Not from there... come this way.

240
00:26:33.055 --> 00:26:33.861 line:82%
Which way?

241
00:26:34.069 --> 00:26:34.899 line:82%
Climb the pipe.

242
00:26:36.986 --> 00:26:37.714 line:82%
This pipe?

243
00:26:52.813 --> 00:26:54.777 line:82%
It's wet... slippery.

244
00:26:56.111 --> 00:26:58.027 line:82%
Wait... I'll get something for you...

245
00:26:58.444 --> 00:26:59.402 line:82%
Okay.

246
00:27:07.027 --> 00:27:08.236 line:82%
Take this.

247
00:27:14.902 --> 00:27:15.944 line:82%
How?

248
00:27:16.736 --> 00:27:17.777 line:82%
I've got a good grip.

249
00:27:17.986 --> 00:27:20.402 line:82%
Okay. Give me 100 Euros.

250
00:27:21.777 --> 00:27:23.111 line:82%
A hundred Euros?

251
00:27:23.902 --> 00:27:25.556 line:82%
What exactly do you do?

252
00:27:26.819 --> 00:27:28.777 line:82%
Do you want to sleep
in that room or not?

253
00:27:29.194 --> 00:27:32.973 line:82%
My friend stays there, but she
is out of town. Hundred Euros?

254
00:27:33.424 --> 00:27:35.861 line:82%
But 100 Euros is a lot...
that's more expensive than hotels.

255
00:27:36.444 --> 00:27:38.736 line:82%
Okay. Then sleep on the bench.

256
00:27:39.986 --> 00:27:43.057 line:82%
Okay, okay. But...

257
00:27:43.902 --> 00:27:46.976 line:82%
Can you take it yourself...
inside the jacket pocket.

258
00:27:51.902 --> 00:27:53.292 line:82%
- Thanks.
- Welcome.

259
00:27:56.402 --> 00:27:57.652 line:82%
What do you do?

260
00:27:58.319 --> 00:27:59.361 line:82%
Me?

261
00:28:10.319 --> 00:28:12.046 line:82%
I'm a writer.

262
00:28:12.444 --> 00:28:14.111 line:82%
What's your business
with the Professor?

263
00:28:14.486 --> 00:28:17.736 line:82%
I'm writing a book on
the finest Indian minds...

264
00:28:18.319 --> 00:28:20.944 line:82%
...and Professor Kidwai
happens to be one of them.

265
00:28:22.091 --> 00:28:23.797 line:82%
So, you're here to interview
the professor?

266
00:28:26.694 --> 00:28:29.861 line:82%
If you interview me later,
that will be a huge help.

267
00:28:30.402 --> 00:28:33.136 line:82%
Yes... why are you
standing on that pipe?

268
00:28:35.527 --> 00:28:37.365 line:82%
Go ahead. Good night.

269
00:28:48.277 --> 00:28:49.361 line:82%
What?

270
00:28:53.694 --> 00:28:54.605 line:82%
Can you cook?

271
00:28:59.020 --> 00:29:01.944 line:82%
Not bad... for an Indian man.

272
00:29:02.944 --> 00:29:04.010 line:82%
Are you married?

273
00:29:04.569 --> 00:29:07.891 line:82%
Straightaway marriage? Won't you
ask me first if I have a girlfriend?

274
00:29:08.282 --> 00:29:12.440 line:82%
No. I think you're old
enough to be married now.

275
00:29:13.246 --> 00:29:16.160 line:82%
No. I'm not married yet.

276
00:29:17.152 --> 00:29:18.194 line:82%
Why?

277
00:29:37.700 --> 00:29:39.026 line:82%
I don't get to meet nice girls.

278
00:29:40.584 --> 00:29:42.122 line:82%
What are you looking for, Mr. Writer?

279
00:29:43.486 --> 00:29:44.569 line:82%
Nothing much...

280
00:29:44.819 --> 00:29:48.641 line:82%
Just a sweet simple girl...

281
00:29:50.611 --> 00:29:57.256 line:82%
Someone who'd make me
want to live only for her.

282
00:29:59.319 --> 00:30:02.576 line:82%
Wow. Very romantic.

283
00:30:02.951 --> 00:30:04.942 line:82%
But you're a bit of a bumpkin
when it comes to style.

284
00:30:05.111 --> 00:30:07.527 line:82%
Really? This is the first time
someone has called me that.

285
00:30:07.940 --> 00:30:09.016 line:82%
What? A bumpkin?

286
00:30:09.902 --> 00:30:11.629 line:82%
No... romantic.

287
00:30:11.902 --> 00:30:13.369 line:82%
And you've been called
a bumpkin before?

288
00:30:14.258 --> 00:30:16.486 line:82%
No... that's a first as well.

289
00:30:18.178 --> 00:30:20.152 line:82%
- Good night Mr Writer.
- Good night, Zoya.

290
00:30:21.152 --> 00:30:23.042 line:82%
The 100 Euros were for
this pass... a play that...

291
00:30:23.319 --> 00:30:25.986 line:82%
I'm going to choreograph...
Professor Kidwai sponsors it.

292
00:30:26.194 --> 00:30:27.791 line:82%
Your breakfast, sir.

293
00:30:29.277 --> 00:30:35.474 line:82%
Excuse me. Can you puncture
the yellow and make it solid?

294
00:30:35.986 --> 00:30:37.404 line:82%
- Okay.
- Thank you.

295
00:30:38.361 --> 00:30:39.402 line:82%
What happened?

296
00:30:39.736 --> 00:30:41.569 line:82%
Aren't you a little fussy
when it comes to food?

297
00:30:41.861 --> 00:30:43.057 line:82%
Maybe a little.

298
00:30:45.861 --> 00:30:48.975 line:82%
So you want to spend some
time with Professor Kidwai?

299
00:30:49.527 --> 00:30:52.111 line:82%
Yes... so that I get
to know him better.

300
00:30:52.759 --> 00:30:55.406 line:82%
I'll try to speak to him.

301
00:30:56.402 --> 00:30:58.100 line:82%
Come to his house tomorrow morning.

302
00:30:58.444 --> 00:30:59.444 line:82%
But I can't promise anything.

303
00:31:00.027 --> 00:31:01.159 line:82%
No problem.

304
00:31:02.319 --> 00:31:03.694 line:82%
Just the way you like it, sir.

305
00:31:04.069 --> 00:31:04.861 line:82%
Thank you.

306
00:31:05.319 --> 00:31:06.361 line:82%
And here's the cheque.

307
00:31:06.651 --> 00:31:08.120 line:82%
Whenever you are ready.

308
00:31:08.902 --> 00:31:12.981 line:82%
I hope you don't mind if I leave
you alone with your punctured eggs.

309
00:31:13.194 --> 00:31:15.805 line:82%
I'm getting late for my play
rehearsal. See you later.

310
00:31:19.194 --> 00:31:21.113 line:82%
You pay the bill... why should I?

311
00:31:23.067 --> 00:31:24.148 line:82%
Yes, of course.

312
00:31:24.402 --> 00:31:26.546 line:82%
You keep puncturing eggs
to eat them...

313
00:31:26.986 --> 00:31:29.194 line:82%
...and make the Indian
government pay for it.

314
00:31:30.236 --> 00:31:33.528 line:82%
Manish Chandra...
isn't that a boring name?

315
00:31:34.069 --> 00:31:35.763 line:82%
I wanted a boring name...

316
00:31:36.055 --> 00:31:39.163 line:82%
...should sound like
a decent guy... right?

317
00:31:39.380 --> 00:31:41.418 line:82%
Look at her gorgeous hair... fire!

318
00:31:43.361 --> 00:31:44.652 line:82%
Okay 'decent guy', listen...

319
00:31:44.861 --> 00:31:46.944 line:82%
...you'll have to get close
to the professor now.

320
00:31:47.277 --> 00:31:49.630 line:82%
I'm thinking people here
are so honest...

321
00:31:49.918 --> 00:31:51.652 line:82%
...they don't even bolt their doors.

322
00:31:51.986 --> 00:31:53.319 line:82%
I should barge into
the professor's house...

323
00:31:53.527 --> 00:31:54.616 line:82%
...and just run off with his computer.

324
00:31:54.812 --> 00:31:56.027 line:82%
Oh, no...

325
00:31:56.486 --> 00:31:59.986 line:82%
Shenoy Sir has clearly instructed
we don't need his computer.

326
00:32:00.425 --> 00:32:02.361 line:82%
All we need to do is keep
an eye on what he does.

327
00:32:02.611 --> 00:32:04.402 line:82%
Who he meets... who he speaks to.

328
00:32:04.819 --> 00:32:06.670 line:82%
The Professor is a nutcase...

329
00:32:07.027 --> 00:32:09.629 line:82%
I'm thinking of entering his
house with the girl's help...

330
00:32:09.905 --> 00:32:11.567 line:82%
...she's calling me tomorrow morning.

331
00:32:11.902 --> 00:32:12.527 line:82%
Good plan.

332
00:32:17.944 --> 00:32:18.980 line:82%
Is he there?

333
00:32:19.236 --> 00:32:19.901 line:82%
Maybe.

334
00:32:21.115 --> 00:32:23.885 line:82%
Sir, I'm writing a book on
the finest Indian minds.

335
00:32:24.569 --> 00:32:27.275 line:82%
I'm just a mad scientist...

336
00:32:27.736 --> 00:32:29.652 line:82%
...at least this is what the
Indian Government thinks.

337
00:32:29.902 --> 00:32:31.968 line:82%
No, sir. You are being modest.

338
00:32:32.372 --> 00:32:34.907 line:82%
Okay... if you insist.

339
00:32:35.277 --> 00:32:36.944 line:82%
Tell me what will I have to do?

340
00:32:37.503 --> 00:32:41.092 line:82%
Sir, I want to spend the maximum
time possible with you.

341
00:32:41.344 --> 00:32:43.470 line:82%
It will be good for the book.

342
00:32:43.762 --> 00:32:46.393 line:82%
For example, when you
make your morning notes...

343
00:32:46.794 --> 00:32:51.319 line:82%
...then I can be with you
when you leave for college.

344
00:32:51.694 --> 00:32:54.236 line:82%
I can be with you in your
office observing your work...

345
00:32:54.444 --> 00:32:55.486 line:82%
...seeing your research.

346
00:32:55.944 --> 00:33:00.402 line:82%
We can talk in your house
when you come back home.

347
00:33:00.902 --> 00:33:05.861 line:82%
Just observe you and be around you,
sir. Like a constant companion.

348
00:33:07.777 --> 00:33:15.586 line:82%
Mr Chandra, are you here to write
a book on me or to marry me?

349
00:33:21.444 --> 00:33:24.819 line:82%
Zoya, why does this damn Rocket
launch himself when he sees me?

350
00:33:25.027 --> 00:33:27.861 line:82%
Hey... don't say that...
Rocket is very sweet.

351
00:33:28.277 --> 00:33:29.704 line:82%
But he keeps barking at me.

352
00:33:29.992 --> 00:33:31.819 line:82%
That's because you swore at him.

353
00:33:32.170 --> 00:33:34.095 line:82%
Hey... but I said it in front of you.

354
00:33:34.652 --> 00:33:36.069 line:82%
Don't you like dogs?

355
00:33:43.944 --> 00:33:46.969 line:82%
No. I do like them.

356
00:33:47.819 --> 00:33:48.694 line:82%
Good.

357
00:33:49.944 --> 00:33:52.242 line:82%
Zoya... your hostel.

358
00:33:53.069 --> 00:33:54.736 line:82%
Yes... bye.

359
00:33:55.085 --> 00:33:58.893 line:82%
Zoya... do you want to...

360
00:33:59.902 --> 00:34:01.277 line:82%
...like have dinner?

361
00:34:02.665 --> 00:34:05.277 line:82%
Mr. Writer, are you asking me
out on a date?

362
00:34:05.616 --> 00:34:06.652 line:82%
Date?

363
00:34:07.319 --> 00:34:09.544 line:82%
No. I mean... we can have a meal.

364
00:34:13.819 --> 00:34:15.907 line:82%
I'm going out with my friends tonight.

365
00:34:16.194 --> 00:34:18.111 line:82%
Join us. I'll let you pay the bill.

366
00:34:18.694 --> 00:34:19.569 line:82%
Sure.

367
00:34:22.736 --> 00:34:24.444 line:82%
But I hope you won't
turn up like this?

368
00:34:26.611 --> 00:34:27.527 line:82%
Like what?

369
00:34:28.986 --> 00:34:31.652 line:82%
You know... dressed like a bumpkin.

370
00:34:33.592 --> 00:34:34.861 line:82%
Just get a little cooler...

371
00:34:38.111 --> 00:34:39.902 line:82%
Keep your foot behind that line.

372
00:34:50.652 --> 00:34:51.319 line:82%
Hey, everybody!!

373
00:34:51.569 --> 00:34:54.444 line:82%
Guys listen. This is my friend
Manish. He's from India.

374
00:34:54.777 --> 00:34:56.680 line:82%
Hey Manish, it's your turn.

375
00:34:58.611 --> 00:35:01.200 line:82%
Have you ever thrown darts?

376
00:35:15.152 --> 00:35:16.111 line:82%
Hello...

377
00:35:16.944 --> 00:35:19.236 line:82%
Dude... all three hit bull's-eye!

378
00:35:20.069 --> 00:35:21.194 line:82%
Are you a writer or James Bond?

379
00:35:21.402 --> 00:35:22.877 line:82%
I know... I know. Won't happen again.

380
00:35:23.111 --> 00:35:25.319 line:82%
This girl is affecting you, my friend.

381
00:35:26.361 --> 00:35:28.319 line:82%
Don't be silly.
It's a part of my job.

382
00:35:28.611 --> 00:35:31.438 line:82%
Fine... and don't drink too much.

383
00:35:31.911 --> 00:35:35.486 line:82%
Okay... mummy dear... bye.

384
00:35:36.027 --> 00:35:38.444 line:82%
Oh, so sweet...
was that your mother on the line?

385
00:35:43.569 --> 00:35:45.861 line:82%
Come on, guys...
we're going to Mike's party.

386
00:35:47.444 --> 00:35:48.569 line:82%
- Do you wanna come?
- No, no.

387
00:35:48.777 --> 00:35:49.944 line:82%
Come on, ya... it will be fun.

388
00:35:50.194 --> 00:35:52.111 line:82%
No. You enjoy. You go.

389
00:35:53.902 --> 00:35:55.236 line:82%
You guys carry on.
I'll see you later.

390
00:35:55.486 --> 00:35:56.986 line:82%
Okay, bye! Cheers!

391
00:35:57.277 --> 00:35:57.861 line:82%
Bye!

392
00:35:58.069 --> 00:35:59.402 line:82%
Hey, but please don't stay
because of me.

393
00:35:59.944 --> 00:36:02.684 line:82%
Why? Now you don't
want to pay for my dinner?

394
00:36:07.152 --> 00:36:08.819 line:82%
No, not Ree... Dee...

395
00:36:09.402 --> 00:36:10.277 line:82%
Ta-ng-dee

396
00:36:10.736 --> 00:36:11.569 line:82%
Tang-Ree

397
00:36:11.986 --> 00:36:13.361 line:82%
Tang... Tang-dee...

398
00:36:13.736 --> 00:36:15.486 line:82%
That's what I said... Tang-ree

399
00:36:15.694 --> 00:36:17.611 line:82%
Do as I say.
Bend your tongue upwards...

400
00:36:17.861 --> 00:36:21.142 line:82%
...and touch it to the roof of
your mouth. Like this...

401
00:36:22.694 --> 00:36:28.527 line:82%
...and now hit your front two
Bugs Bunny teeth with it... Dee!

402
00:36:28.777 --> 00:36:29.652 line:82%
Ree...

403
00:36:30.986 --> 00:36:31.569 line:82%
Dee...

404
00:36:31.777 --> 00:36:32.694 line:82%
- Tang-dee...
- Correct!

405
00:36:32.861 --> 00:36:33.527 line:82%
See... right?

406
00:36:33.694 --> 00:36:34.444 line:82%
Now place the order.

407
00:36:34.703 --> 00:36:35.428 line:82%
Okay.

408
00:36:35.604 --> 00:36:36.445 line:82%
- Yes ma'am.
- Hi.

409
00:36:36.633 --> 00:36:38.078 line:82%
Two... Tang-ree kebabs.

410
00:36:38.486 --> 00:36:40.921 line:82%
Go ahead, my friend.
Get Tang-ree kebabs.

411
00:36:41.193 --> 00:36:42.034 line:82%
No problem, Sir.

412
00:36:44.039 --> 00:36:45.301 line:82%
You know what?

413
00:36:46.627 --> 00:36:47.944 line:82%
You don't look like a writer.

414
00:36:53.111 --> 00:36:54.069 line:82%
For example...

415
00:36:54.444 --> 00:36:56.926 line:82%
...your hands...
they are not like a writer's...

416
00:36:57.277 --> 00:36:59.986 line:82%
...they're cut and bruised
like a wrestler's.

417
00:37:00.986 --> 00:37:02.811 line:82%
Why did you become a writer?

418
00:37:04.819 --> 00:37:07.569 line:82%
Just followed my heart.

419
00:37:08.236 --> 00:37:12.152 line:82%
Very few people follow
their hearts. You're lucky.

420
00:37:14.819 --> 00:37:17.944 line:82%
The most important
thing for an agent is...

421
00:37:18.277 --> 00:37:21.826 line:82%
...that he should use his
head and not his heart.

422
00:37:22.126 --> 00:37:27.317 line:82%
The day you follow your heart,
consider yourself dead.

423
00:37:29.902 --> 00:37:31.611 line:82%
I admire a man who follows his heart.

424
00:37:35.111 --> 00:37:36.277 line:82%
Tang-dee kabab for you, sir...

425
00:37:37.652 --> 00:37:40.364 line:82%
...and ma'am... for you Tang-ree.
Enjoy.

426
00:37:42.527 --> 00:37:44.601 line:82%
What the hell,
Gopi you kept coughing.

427
00:37:44.861 --> 00:37:47.884 line:82%
What if she saw you.
I've reached. I'll call you back.

428
00:38:06.694 --> 00:38:08.383 line:82%
But Tiger, he could have been
a burglar.

429
00:38:08.652 --> 00:38:09.896 line:82%
No, Gopi.

430
00:38:10.402 --> 00:38:14.361 line:82%
The way he attacked me...
he was obviously trained.

431
00:38:14.944 --> 00:38:18.570 line:82%
Someone is reacting on seeing me
with the Professor.

432
00:38:18.944 --> 00:38:20.277 line:82%
Boss, things are not good here.

433
00:38:20.527 --> 00:38:21.736 line:82%
We'll have to wrap this up quickly.

434
00:38:22.027 --> 00:38:23.669 line:82%
That's why we're here.

435
00:38:29.111 --> 00:38:30.402 line:82%
How's this?

436
00:38:31.361 --> 00:38:32.789 line:82%
What will you do with it?

437
00:38:33.277 --> 00:38:34.111 line:82%
It's a gift.

438
00:38:34.486 --> 00:38:35.527 line:82%
And it's a gift for whom?

439
00:38:35.944 --> 00:38:38.111 line:82%
For Zoya... to say thank you.

440
00:38:39.236 --> 00:38:40.542 line:82%
Wow, Tiger!

441
00:38:40.944 --> 00:38:43.065 line:82%
You've used people all over
the world and discarded them...

442
00:38:43.277 --> 00:38:44.986 line:82%
...since when have you
started saying thank you?

443
00:38:45.402 --> 00:38:47.055 line:82%
Gopi... this is a different
sort of a mission...

444
00:38:47.319 --> 00:38:48.652 line:82%
...here it's important
to say thank you.

445
00:38:48.944 --> 00:38:49.917 line:82%
Which mission?

446
00:38:50.125 --> 00:38:51.861 line:82%
Ours? Or have you started
another mission?

447
00:38:52.111 --> 00:38:54.304 line:82%
Stop your nonsense and tell me
what you think of this.

448
00:38:56.444 --> 00:38:57.444 line:82%
Isn't this too personal?

449
00:38:58.777 --> 00:38:59.319 line:82%
What?

450
00:38:59.527 --> 00:39:01.314 line:82%
I mean... do you know her that
well that you can give her a dress?

451
00:39:01.819 --> 00:39:03.152 line:82%
I'm giving her a dress...
not taking it off.

452
00:39:15.277 --> 00:39:19.326 line:82%
Tiger, you've never bought a gift for
a girl ever in your life... have you?

453
00:39:19.694 --> 00:39:20.569 line:82%
Never.

454
00:39:20.861 --> 00:39:21.777 line:82%
Then what's going on here?

455
00:39:22.611 --> 00:39:23.444 line:82%
What?

456
00:39:23.819 --> 00:39:27.565 line:82%
Hey... it's extremely important
to woo Zoya for this mission.

457
00:39:28.694 --> 00:39:29.792 line:82%
What?

458
00:39:30.173 --> 00:39:32.643 line:82%
Don't get wooed yourself
in the process.

459
00:39:39.736 --> 00:39:40.569 line:82%
