758
01:15:32.942 --> 01:15:35.055 line:82%
If the gun was in your hand...

759
01:15:35.984 --> 01:15:37.317 line:82%
I would have still said
the same thing.

760
01:15:37.567 --> 01:15:39.695 line:82%
It's not as easy as you think...

761
01:15:40.067 --> 01:15:43.359 line:82%
...the other agent who you killed...

762
01:15:43.580 --> 01:15:45.247 line:82%
Feroz... he was also right there.

763
01:15:47.817 --> 01:15:53.234 line:82%
A girl... whose training and duty
forbids her from falling in love...

764
01:15:54.526 --> 01:15:57.776 line:82%
...to whom could she say that yes,
she too was in love?

765
01:16:01.651 --> 01:16:05.116 line:82%
To the man whose real name
she didn't know?

766
01:16:05.692 --> 01:16:07.565 line:82%
To the man who was pointing
a gun at her?

767
01:16:10.901 --> 01:16:13.192 line:82%
And even had I said that...
what good would it have done?

768
01:16:14.151 --> 01:16:17.010 line:82%
The two of us can never be together.

769
01:16:19.109 --> 01:16:20.609 line:82%
And what does it mean to be together?

770
01:16:21.234 --> 01:16:23.417 line:82%
That we come and shake hands
every month at the Wagah border?

771
01:16:24.401 --> 01:16:27.467 line:82%
Or send song requests for
one another on All India Radio?

772
01:16:28.192 --> 01:16:30.192 line:82%
I'm ISI... you're RAW.

773
01:16:32.901 --> 01:16:34.539 line:82%
We are enemies.

774
01:16:34.984 --> 01:16:37.352 line:82%
Our duty won't let us be together.

775
01:16:38.651 --> 01:16:40.609 line:82%
Our people won't let us be together.

776
01:16:42.651 --> 01:16:45.180 line:82%
You know they'll come after us.

777
01:16:56.567 --> 01:16:58.139 line:82%
Yes, Captain Abrar...

778
