We're not going to Kazakhstan.

922
01:32:16.817 --> 01:32:17.901 line:82%
Then where are we going?

923
01:32:18.484 --> 01:32:20.317 line:82%
Let's see. Come quickly.

924
01:33:07.276 --> 01:33:08.276 line:82%
You knew all along?

925
01:33:10.317 --> 01:33:13.067 line:82%
I was an agent before
I became a lover.

926
01:33:13.734 --> 01:33:20.026 line:82%
But I had to do this because of
your drama at the ballroom that day.

927
01:33:21.317 --> 01:33:22.984 line:82%
Captain Abrar saw you and said...

928
01:33:23.234 --> 01:33:25.748 line:82%
...this prey has happily
walked to a trap.

929
01:33:26.484 --> 01:33:29.056 line:82%
And right then...
he made a plan to get you.

930
01:33:30.109 --> 01:33:32.776 line:82%
But if you saw me
with Captain Abrar...

931
01:33:34.026 --> 01:33:35.609 line:82%
...then why did you come
to the airport with me?

932
01:33:35.859 --> 01:33:39.067 line:82%
Zoya... all my life
I've used only my head.

933
01:33:40.567 --> 01:33:44.155 line:82%
For once I followed my heart...

934
01:33:45.109 --> 01:33:48.776 line:82%
I just wanted to see where
this decision would take me.

935
01:33:58.276 --> 01:34:02.219 line:82%
I'm amused at the thought of
what will happen in Kazakhstan now.

936
01:34:10.151 --> 01:34:11.736 line:82%
Seen anyone like her?

937
01:34:13.168 --> 01:34:15.665 line:82%
See there... in that car.

938
01:34:16.526 --> 01:34:19.151 line:82%
They look like bloody Indians.

939
01:34:19.624 --> 01:34:21.401 line:82%
Pakistani goons...

940
01:34:30.401 --> 01:34:31.234 line:82%
Captain Abrar.

941
01:34:31.442 --> 01:34:32.692 line:82%
Gopi, sir.

942
01:34:32.984 --> 01:34:36.317 line:82%
Sir... it's been close to four hours
since the Istanbul flight landed...

943
01:34:36.609 --> 01:34:37.734 line:82%
...and no one has shown up.

944
01:34:37.942 --> 01:34:38.609 line:82%
Alright.

945
01:34:42.651 --> 01:34:45.337 line:82%
Sir... the information
about Kazakhstan was wrong.

946
01:34:46.484 --> 01:34:47.930 line:82%
No one arrived there today.

947
01:34:50.192 --> 01:34:52.151 line:82%
There were two other big flights
that left Istanbul yesterday.

948
01:34:52.401 --> 01:34:53.859 line:82%
One to London and
the other to Frankfurt.

949
01:34:55.109 --> 01:34:57.984 line:82%
Then find out from there how
many other flights departed.

950
01:34:58.734 --> 01:35:00.442 line:82%
Sir... there are 623 flights
at London...

951
01:35:00.608 --> 01:35:02.484 line:82%
...and 612 flights at Frankfurt
scheduled to take off today...

952
01:35:02.692 --> 01:35:05.859 line:82%
...total number of passengers
825,802...

953
01:35:06.234 --> 01:35:08.109 line:82%
...and those two could be traveling
on a passport of any nationality...

954
01:35:08.317 --> 01:35:09.692 line:82%
I don't care.

955
01:35:10.901 --> 01:35:13.659 line:82%
Keep searching...
we have to find them.

956
01:35:15.651 --> 01:35:17.098 line:82%
Sir... my point is...

957
01:35:17.734 --> 01:35:20.859 line:82%
...if Tiger has decided... then it
will be very difficult to find him.

958
01:35:21.401 --> 01:35:23.436 line:82%
We have created Tiger!

959
01:35:27.442 --> 01:35:29.571 line:82%
RAW was functioning before him...

960
01:35:30.692 --> 01:35:32.609 line:82%
...and will continue even after him.

961
01:35:39.442 --> 01:35:40.276 line:82%
Gopi...

962
01:35:41.984 --> 01:35:45.484 line:82%
The amount of information that
Tiger has about our organization...

963
01:35:46.609 --> 01:35:51.083 line:82%
...before ISI gets that information...

964
01:35:52.067 --> 01:35:55.484 line:82%
...we have to find Tiger
and bring him back.

965
01:35:59.692 --> 01:36:01.401 line:82%
And... if he doesn't want to return?

966
01:36:05.776 --> 01:36:10.764 line:82%
Then I'm sure you know
what we must do...

967
01:36:13.317 --> 01:36:15.129 line:82%
Just remember...

968
01:36:16.526 --> 01:36:20.615 line:82%
...no one should be able
to identify his body.

969
01:36:26.037 --> 01:36:27.634 line:82%
HAVANA - CUBA

970
01:37:05.192 --> 01:37:07.124 line:82%
Keep your eyes closed

971
01:37:07.442 --> 01:37:09.317 line:82%
And count slowly

972
01:37:09.651 --> 01:37:12.526 line:82%
Find me for I don't know where I am

973
01:37:14.067 --> 01:37:16.026 line:82%
Forgotten are our tales

974
01:37:16.317 --> 01:37:18.317 line:82%
We are strangers to our own land

975
01:37:18.567 --> 01:37:21.067 line:82%
See how we have turned into thin air

976
01:37:22.609 --> 01:37:24.317 line:82%
Close to the heart

977
01:37:24.901 --> 01:37:26.442 line:82%
Under the sheet of dreams

978
01:37:27.067 --> 01:37:28.401 line:82%
Is this lost world

979
01:37:28.817 --> 01:37:30.192 line:82%
Of ours

980
01:37:31.026 --> 01:37:32.484 line:82%
I am lost

981
01:37:35.484 --> 01:37:36.901 line:82%
You are lost

982
01:37:39.942 --> 01:37:41.442 line:82%
All our senses

983
01:37:44.317 --> 01:37:45.901 line:82%
Are all lost

984
01:38:25.192 --> 01:38:28.401 line:82%
Yes this is my wish

985
01:38:29.651 --> 01:38:32.609 line:82%
To think of only you

986
01:38:34.026 --> 01:38:37.484 line:82%
The glow that emanates from you

987
01:38:38.401 --> 01:38:41.567 line:82%
Will remain captured in my dreams

988
01:38:42.151 --> 01:38:44.234 line:82%
When did morning fall asleep?

989
01:38:44.901 --> 01:38:46.442 line:82%
When did the stars awaken?

990
01:38:47.067 --> 01:38:48.442 line:82%
We have forgotten...

991
01:38:48.817 --> 01:38:50.276 line:82%
...what happens when

992
01:38:51.067 --> 01:38:52.734 line:82%
I am lost

993
01:38:55.484 --> 01:38:56.609 line:82%
You are lost

994
01:38:59.901 --> 01:39:01.317 line:82%
All our senses

995
01:39:04.359 --> 01:39:05.984 line:82%
Are all lost

996
01:39:45.192 --> 01:39:47.984 line:82%
Yes I was breathing

997
01:39:49.651 --> 01:39:52.917 line:82%
But I was never alive

998
01:39:54.109 --> 01:39:57.647 line:82%
When I gave my heart away to you

999
01:39:58.567 --> 01:40:01.657 line:82%
I realized what a heartbeat was...

1000
01:40:02.109 --> 01:40:04.276 line:82%
Immersed in you

1001
01:40:04.901 --> 01:40:06.526 line:82%
Lost in you

1002
01:40:07.151 --> 01:40:08.484 line:82%
Away from you

1003
01:40:08.817 --> 01:40:10.442 line:82%
Where do I go?

1004
01:40:11.067 --> 01:40:12.901 line:82%
I am lost

1005
01:40:15.484 --> 01:40:17.309 line:82%
You are lost

1006
01:40:19.942 --> 01:40:21.484 line:82%
All our senses

1007
01:40:24.359 --> 01:40:26.151 line:82%
Are all lost

1008
01:40:45.317 --> 01:40:46.548 line:82%
What does it mean?

1009
01:40:49.026 --> 01:40:50.692 line:82%
Sane love...

1010
01:40:51.734 --> 01:40:53.151 line:82%
...is no love

1011
01:40:55.567 --> 01:40:56.234 line:82%
Wow!

1012
01:41:36.609 --> 01:41:38.067 line:82%
Give me your money!

1013
01:41:39.859 --> 01:41:40.901 line:82%
Give me your money!

1014
01:41:43.609 --> 01:41:46.276 line:82%
Give me your money!

1015
01:42:39.442 --> 01:42:42.067 line:82%
Zoya... let's get out of here.

1016
01:42:45.942 --> 01:42:48.484 line:82%
Zoya... let's get out of here.

1017
01:42:48.984 --> 01:42:50.651 line:82%
What language is it?

1018
01:42:51.401 --> 01:42:52.734 line:82%
Is it Arabic?

1019
01:42:53.692 --> 01:42:56.692 line:82%
No, not Arabic... sounds like...
Hindi or Bengali...

1020
01:42:57.234 --> 01:43:05.901 line:82%
Spoken in India, Pakistan,
Bangladesh, Afghanistan.

1021
01:43:08.137 --> 01:43:09.720 line:82%
NEW DELHI 10:30 P.M.

1022
01:43:10.234 --> 01:43:13.638 line:82%
Dayal. Why have you sent me this?

1023
01:43:13.901 --> 01:43:17.091 line:82%
Don't send me Embassy correspondence.

1024
01:43:17.984 --> 01:43:21.372 line:82%
You should be able to
handle this at your level.

1025
01:43:22.026 --> 01:43:24.526 line:82%
My brains get fried
with all this nonsense...

1026
01:43:24.817 --> 01:43:27.190 line:82%
...and especially when
I'm ready to go home...

1027
01:43:46.651 --> 01:43:47.692 line:82%
Which embassy?

1028
01:43:48.734 --> 01:43:50.651 line:82%
Havana, sir. Cuba.

1029
01:44:00.026 --> 01:44:02.320 line:82%
Honeymoon's over... Tiger.

1030
01:44:28.234 --> 01:44:29.567 line:82%
We're being watched.

1031
01:44:33.651 --> 01:44:34.692 line:82%
Eleven o' clock.

1032
01:44:37.984 --> 01:44:40.401 line:82%
You are right. We are being watched.

1033
01:45:15.484 --> 01:45:17.567 line:82%
Can you please come
back in 20 minutes?

1034
01:45:19.151 --> 01:45:19.776 line:82%
Yes, Zoya?

1035
01:45:19.942 --> 01:45:21.901 line:82%
They are saying that they need
the manager's authorisation...

1036
01:45:22.151 --> 01:45:24.667 line:82%
...for such a big amount...
and he's not there.

1037
01:45:24.984 --> 01:45:26.692 line:82%
...right now they can only
give half of that amount.

1038
01:45:27.109 --> 01:45:28.151 line:82%
Okay... get that for now.

1039
01:45:43.026 --> 01:45:45.442 line:82%
The manager will be back in 20
minutes. This is all I could get.

1040
01:45:45.859 --> 01:45:47.667 line:82%
I will get a car with the money.

1041
01:45:47.942 --> 01:45:49.401 line:82%
You withdraw the rest of
the money from the bank.

1042
01:45:50.317 --> 01:45:53.048 line:82%
Don't worry. We'll be
out of here by evening.

1043
01:46:07.192 --> 01:46:08.734 line:82%
Police please?

1044
01:46:22.692 --> 01:46:25.359 line:82%
Stop now... you've run enough.

1045
01:46:37.401 --> 01:46:39.711 line:82%
Zoya, look what I found.

1046
01:46:40.317 --> 01:46:42.358 line:82%
Willy's jeep. The same '52 model.

1047
01:46:45.442 --> 01:46:48.901 line:82%
Oh... I'm sorry, I didn't mean
to remind you of your father.

1048
01:46:55.151 --> 01:46:56.401 line:82%
What happened?

1049
01:46:57.030 --> 01:46:58.359 line:82%
It's over.

1050
01:47:02.026 --> 01:47:03.401 line:82%
They were waiting for you.

1051
01:47:04.192 --> 01:47:06.026 line:82%
We have to go and sit in that car.

1052
01:47:33.567 --> 01:47:34.901 line:82%
Tiger, don't try anything here.

1053
01:47:35.817 --> 01:47:39.650 line:82%
I know... they will kill
us here if they have to.

1054
01:47:45.692 --> 01:47:46.651 line:82%
Come...

1055
01:48:25.109 --> 01:48:26.651 line:82%
Follow them... fast!

1056
01:48:27.442 --> 01:48:28.359 line:82%
Hurry up!

1057
01:49:21.734 --> 01:49:22.901 line:82%
Hey, stop.

1058
01:49:23.609 --> 01:49:24.567 line:82%
Wait... wait.

1059
01:49:29.901 --> 01:49:30.859 line:82%
Thank you.

1060
01:49:39.018 --> 01:49:39.818 line:82%
This way.

1061
01:50:41.859 --> 01:50:43.817 line:82%
Tiger... Tiger, come on! Fast!

1062
01:51:19.984 --> 01:51:20.984 line:82%
Stop it, Zoya!

1063
01:51:24.234 --> 01:51:25.192 line:82%
Enough!

1064
01:55:03.817 --> 01:55:06.067 line:82%
What is it that they
have and we don't?

1065
01:55:06.293 --> 01:55:07.264 line:82%
Five minutes are more than enough.

1066
01:55:07.398 --> 01:55:10.138 line:82%
I don't care. If you have
to shoot him... then do it.

1067
01:55:15.942 --> 01:55:17.109 line:82%
I'll call you back.

1068
01:55:17.442 --> 01:55:20.026 line:82%
So, Gopi... you want me to be shot?

1069
01:55:20.328 --> 01:55:21.567 line:82%
You deserve to be shot.

1070
01:55:21.942 --> 01:55:22.734 line:82%
What have I done?

1071
01:55:23.026 --> 01:55:24.473 line:82%
What have you done?

1072
01:55:26.151 --> 01:55:28.613 line:82%
Tiger, do you know how many
countries there are in the world?

1073
01:55:29.151 --> 01:55:33.276 line:82%
201 countries. There are
201 countries and you.

1074
01:55:33.468 --> 01:55:37.567 line:82%
203... after Kosovo
separated from Serbia.

1075
01:55:38.609 --> 01:55:39.484 line:82%
Okay...

1076
01:55:40.192 --> 01:55:42.234 line:82%
203 countries and you...

1077
01:55:42.418 --> 01:55:44.776 line:82%
No... 204...

1078
01:55:45.442 --> 01:55:47.359 line:82%
...because Montenegro also
separated from Serbia.

1079
01:55:47.651 --> 01:55:49.817 line:82%
I don't care whether there
are 203 or 204 countries!

1080
01:55:50.317 --> 01:55:52.234 line:82%
How can you elope with a Pakistani?

1081
01:55:53.442 --> 01:55:58.359 line:82%
Gopi... do you know how much
information Zoya can provide us?

1082
01:55:59.234 --> 01:56:00.442 line:82%
Do you have any idea?

1083
01:56:01.442 --> 01:56:03.401 line:82%
Zoya is ready to come to India
with us.

1084
01:56:05.317 --> 01:56:06.359 line:82%
Really?

1085
01:56:08.692 --> 01:56:09.609 line:82%
Then where is she?

1086
01:56:09.817 --> 01:56:10.972 line:82%
Call her... let's leave.

1087
01:56:12.859 --> 01:56:17.276 line:82%
For that I'll need you and your boys.

1088
01:56:17.901 --> 01:56:19.776 line:82%
Why? You just told
me that she's ready.

1089
01:56:20.317 --> 01:56:22.567 line:82%
Yes but those people
who she is with right now...

1090
01:56:22.817 --> 01:56:24.984 line:82%
...won't let her come
to India that easily.

1091
01:56:26.317 --> 01:56:27.276 line:82%
Who are they?

1092
01:56:27.984 --> 01:56:29.067 line:82%
Our friends...

1093
01:56:33.151 --> 01:56:34.947 line:82%
So let me get this straight.

1094
01:56:35.234 --> 01:56:39.467 line:82%
You want us to attack
the ISI in Cuba.

1095
01:56:39.817 --> 01:56:42.765 line:82%
Why? To kidnap a girl?

1096
01:56:44.151 --> 01:56:45.109 line:82%
Girl?

1097
01:56:46.442 --> 01:56:48.484 line:82%
The same girl was your
sister-in-law in Dublin...

1098
01:56:48.942 --> 01:56:51.089 line:82%
...when you found out
she was a Pakistani...

1099
01:56:51.692 --> 01:56:54.047 line:82%
...you demoted her from
sister-in-law to just a girl?

1100
01:56:56.651 --> 01:56:59.853 line:82%
Gopi... they are flying her to
Pakistan tomorrow morning.

1101
01:57:01.359 --> 01:57:02.567 line:82%
Hey caveman...

1102
01:57:02.942 --> 01:57:04.904 line:82%
...whatever needs to be done,
should be done now.

1103
01:57:09.151 --> 01:57:10.420 line:82%
What will Shenoy sir say?

1104
01:57:13.317 --> 01:57:16.859 line:82%
Tiger... Tiger... Tiger.

1105
01:57:17.776 --> 01:57:19.192 line:82%
What the hell is Tiger doing?

1106
01:57:26.151 --> 01:57:28.942 line:82%
That's the plan...
Tokas, you will be here.

1107
01:57:29.401 --> 01:57:29.942 line:82%
Sir.

1108
01:57:30.151 --> 01:57:31.692 line:82%
Bablu... you'll be at this point.

1109
01:57:31.984 --> 01:57:33.776 line:82%
Jassi, you will block them from here.

1110
01:57:34.026 --> 01:57:34.942 line:82%
Tiger... take this.

1111
01:57:35.151 --> 01:57:36.359 line:82%
Thanks, Gopi.

1112
01:57:37.067 --> 01:57:42.109 line:82%
You, caveman... you got an
entire army just to catch me?

1113
01:57:43.067 --> 01:57:44.859 line:82%
Sir... don't forget we came here
to catch that man...

1114
01:57:45.192 --> 01:57:46.317 line:82%
...from whom we learnt everything.

1115
01:57:46.526 --> 01:57:49.692 line:82%
One last time... you'll be here.

1116
01:57:50.401 --> 01:57:51.817 line:82%
Tomorrow morning sharp at eight.

1117
01:58:07.901 --> 01:58:09.817 line:82%
Our flight will take
off in two hours.

1118
01:58:11.151 --> 01:58:14.151 line:82%
Don't try anything strange
at the airport.

1119
01:58:19.192 --> 01:58:21.026 line:82%
Nothing is more precious
in the world for a woman...

1120
01:58:21.276 --> 01:58:23.688 line:82%
...than her honour and dignity.

1121
01:58:31.609 --> 01:58:34.067 line:82%
And that Indian friend of yours...

1122
01:58:35.489 --> 01:58:37.873 line:82%
...he left you alone and
disappeared really fast?

1123
01:58:49.109 --> 01:58:49.984 line:82%
Come on, come on!

1124
01:59:15.567 --> 01:59:17.484 line:82%
Come on, come on! Go, go!

1125
01:59:48.526 --> 01:59:49.942 line:82%
Hurry! Follow them, quick!

1126
01:59:57.526 --> 02:00:00.109 line:82%
You rascal... God made
you and broke that mould!

1127
02:00:01.317 --> 02:00:02.192 line:82%
Sister-in-law!

1128
02:00:15.984 --> 02:00:17.192 line:82%
Turn around! Now!

1129
02:00:27.692 --> 02:00:28.704 line:82%
Turn left!

1130
02:01:49.609 --> 02:01:51.871 line:82%
Come on, go go! Airpark!

1131
02:01:52.234 --> 02:01:53.651 line:82%
Come on! Move fast!

1132
02:02:17.692 --> 02:02:18.817 line:82%
Stop! Stop there!

1133
02:02:32.567 --> 02:02:34.151 line:82%
I will make it...
don't worry about me...

1134
02:02:34.359 --> 02:02:36.026 line:82%
...don't stop the plane
for anything...

1135
02:02:36.359 --> 02:02:38.192 line:82%
...we'll get just this one chance
for take off!

1136
02:03:16.734 --> 02:03:17.651 line:82%
Go, go, go!

1137
02:03:17.818 --> 02:03:18.579 line:82%
Cut them off!

1138
02:05:17.431 --> 02:05:20.685 line:82%
Hey, pilot... fly me to a safe place.

1139
02:05:40.859 --> 02:05:41.901 line:82%
Hello.

1140
02:05:42.484 --> 02:05:43.567 line:82%
Hello?

1141
02:05:44.067 --> 02:05:45.569 line:82%
Shenoy sir.

1142
02:05:54.442 --> 02:05:56.859 line:82%
Speak up... Avinash Singh Rathore.

1143
02:05:57.276 --> 02:06:01.535 line:82%
You've called me by my real
name for the very first time.

1144
02:06:02.067 --> 02:06:04.442 line:82%
You've shown your true
colours for the first time.

1145
02:06:04.859 --> 02:06:08.859 line:82%
No, sir... for the first time in
my life I truly followed by heart.

1146
02:06:09.359 --> 02:06:11.750 line:82%
You forgot your duty.

1147
02:06:12.567 --> 02:06:14.546 line:82%
No, sir. I never forget my duty.

1148
02:06:14.859 --> 02:06:16.526 line:82%
I remember my duty... my training.

1149
02:06:17.192 --> 02:06:21.334 line:82%
But I also understand that beyond
them Tiger is a human being too.

1150
02:06:21.817 --> 02:06:25.692 line:82%
You yourself said once...
it's not easy to live with regrets.

1151
02:06:26.734 --> 02:06:29.484 line:82%
To love your enemy is treachery.

